        <p>Shipping live cargo is the part scammers gloss over and we don't: fertile eggs travel cradled in a foam-lined insulated carton with a heat pack, while a reserved chick flies IATA live-animal cargo on the two delivery tiers below. Even done right, shipped eggs carry more risk than local pickup — and you deserve to hear that before you order.</p>
